form_title.ms_form_title_llm_v1: Notice of Naturalization Oath Ceremony, N-4-4-5-4-4-4-4-1-1-1-5-0-0-0-5-2

full_text: Screened by NARA, 8/2/2023 U.S. Department of Justice OMB #1115-0052 Immigration and Naturalization Service Notice of Naturalization Oath Ceremony Naturalization and Citizenship Branch 300 NOR TH LOS ANGELES STREET File or A # A28 700 722 LOS ANGELES, CA 90012 9/01/1993 Date You are hereby notified to appear for a Naturalization Oath Ceremony at the DATE, TIME AND PLACE SHOWN BELOW. 10/20/1993 Date SANT DUA 8:00 AM 11111 STRATHERN ST #9 Time SUN VALLEY CA 91352 more LOS ANGELES CONVENTI ION CENTER Place 1201 SOUTH FIGUERDA STREET LOS ANGELES, CA 90012 PROPER COURT ROOM ATTIRE IS REQUIRED ROOM NUMBER: HALL ILITARY PROONNEL PLEASE WEAR UNIFORM You must bring the following with you: This letter, with ALL of the QUESTIONS ON THE REVERSE side answered in ink or on a typewriter Alien Registration Card. Reentry Permit or Refugee Travel Document. AIU Any immigration documents you may have. If the naturalization application is ON BEHALF OF YOUR CHILD (children), BRING your CHILD (children). If you cannot come to this ceremony, return this notice immediately and state why you cannot appear. In such case, please use the return address in the extreme upper left hand corner of this letter. You will be sent another notice of ceremony at a later date. You must appear at an oath ceremony to complete the naturalization process. Form N-445A (Rev. 1/8/92) IMPORTANT - PLEASE SEE REVERSE
